01:49:39.740 --> 01:49:41.880
but rather in a modulatory way,

01:49:41.880 --> 01:49:44.760
but it appears that phosphatidylserine

01:49:44.760 --> 01:49:49.690
taken for two months for
200 milligrams per day,

01:49:49.690 --> 01:49:52.980
was able to reduce the
symptoms of ADHD in children.

01:49:52.980 --> 01:49:55.430
It has not been looked
at in adults yet as,

01:49:55.430 --> 01:49:57.270
at least as far as I know,

01:49:57.270 --> 01:50:00.610
but that this effect was greatly enhanced

01:50:00.610 --> 01:50:03.570
by the consumption of omega-3 fatty acids.

01:50:03.570 --> 01:50:05.710
So now we're starting to
see synergistic effects

01:50:05.710 --> 01:50:08.010
of omega-3 fatty acids
and phosphatidylserine

01:50:08.930 --> 01:50:11.210
again that was 200 milligrams per day.

01:50:11.210 --> 01:50:12.280
This is something that sold

01:50:12.280 --> 01:50:15.250
over the counter in capsule
form, at least in the U.S.

01:50:15.250 --> 01:50:16.490
there were two studies,

01:50:16.490 --> 01:50:18.310
both were double-blind studies.

01:50:18.310 --> 01:50:21.870
I carried out for anywhere
from one to six months on both

01:50:21.870 --> 01:50:23.780
boys and girls and it
really was boys and girls,

01:50:23.780 --> 01:50:24.790
not men and women.

01:50:24.790 --> 01:50:28.860
This was kids age one
to six or seven to 12,

01:50:28.860 --> 01:50:32.160
and it was a fairly
large number of subjects.

01:50:32.160 --> 01:50:35.570
So 147 subjects in one
