01:56:19.130 --> 01:56:20.000
Now you may notice that

01:56:20.000 --> 01:56:22.800
I haven't talked much about acetylcholine.

01:56:22.800 --> 01:56:24.960
Acetylcholine is a neurotransmitter

01:56:24.960 --> 01:56:27.010
that at the neuron to muscle connections,

01:56:27.010 --> 01:56:28.880
the so called neuromuscular junctions

01:56:28.880 --> 01:56:30.880
is involved in generating
muscular contractions

01:56:30.880 --> 01:56:32.823
of all kinds for all movements.

01:56:34.120 --> 01:56:37.190
Acetylcholine is also released
from two sites in the brain.

01:56:37.190 --> 01:56:38.980
So a little bit of
nomenclature here again,

01:56:38.980 --> 01:56:41.080
feel free to ignore the nomenclature,

01:56:41.080 --> 01:56:43.720
but there is a collection of
neurons in your brain stem

01:56:43.720 --> 01:56:45.100
that send projections forward,

01:56:45.100 --> 01:56:46.600
kind of like a sprinkler system

01:56:46.600 --> 01:56:50.060
that's very diffuse to
release acetylcholine

01:56:50.060 --> 01:56:53.680
and those neurons reside
in an area or a structure

01:56:53.680 --> 01:56:57.260
that's called the
pedunculopontine nucleus, the PPN

01:56:57.260 --> 01:56:59.380
and then there's a separate
collection of neurons

01:56:59.380 --> 01:57:02.068
in the basal forebrain called

01:57:02.068 --> 01:57:05.750
unimaginatively nucleus
basalis the nucleus at the base

01:57:05.750 --> 01:57:09.300
and they also hose the
brain with acetylcholine,

01:57:09.300 --> 01:57:11.850
but in a much more specific way.

01:57:11.850 --> 01:57:13.497
So one is sort of like a sprinkler system

01:57:13.497 --> 01:57:15.430
and the other one is more like a fire hose

01:57:15.430 --> 01:57:16.510
to a particular location

01:57:16.510 --> 01:57:19.003
and those two sources of acetylcholine,

01:57:19.960 --> 01:57:23.810
collaborate to activate
particular locations in the brain,

01:57:23.810 --> 01:57:26.540
and really bring about a
tremendous degree of focus

01:57:26.540 --> 01:57:29.740
to whatever is happening at
those particular synapses.

01:57:29.740 --> 01:57:32.020
So it could be a focus
on visual information

01:57:32.020 --> 01:57:33.230
or auditory information,

01:57:33.230 --> 01:57:35.677
if you're listening closely
to what I'm saying right now,

01:57:35.677 --> 01:57:37.320
and you just heard closely

01:57:37.320 --> 01:57:39.420
step out from the rest of my sentence,

01:57:39.420 --> 01:57:41.310
no doubt there was acetylcholine

01:57:41.310 --> 01:57:43.220
released at the sites in your brain

01:57:43.220 --> 01:57:46.590
where the neurons that
represent your recognition

01:57:46.590 --> 01:57:49.290
of the word closely occurred, okay?

01:57:49.290 --> 01:57:51.370
So now you have an example
and you have an understanding

01:57:51.370 --> 01:57:52.530
and hopefully a picture in your mind

01:57:52.530 --> 01:57:54.261
of how all this is working,

01:57:54.261 --> 01:57:58.270
not surprisingly then drugs
that increase cholinergic

01:57:58.270 --> 01:57:59.845
or acetycholine transmission

01:57:59.845 --> 01:58:03.003
will increase focus and cognition.

01:58:03.003 --> 01:58:06.420
One such compound is so-called alpha GPC,

01:58:06.420 --> 01:58:09.970
which is a form of choline
and increases acetycholine

01:58:09.970 --> 01:58:14.660
transmission dosages as high
as 1200 milligrams per day,

01:58:14.660 --> 01:58:16.530
which has a very high dosage spread out,

01:58:16.530 --> 01:58:19.610
typically it's 300 or
400 milligrams spread out

01:58:19.610 --> 01:58:23.170
throughout the day have
been shown to offset

01:58:23.170 --> 01:58:26.260
some of the effects of
age-related cognitive decline,

01:58:26.260 --> 01:58:27.490
improved cognitive functioning

01:58:27.490 --> 01:58:29.600
people that don't have
age-related cognitive decline

01:58:29.600 --> 01:58:30.980
that's a very high dose.

01:58:30.980 --> 01:58:34.750
Typically when people are
using alpha-GPC to study

01:58:34.750 --> 01:58:36.930
or to enhance learning of any kind,

01:58:36.930 --> 01:58:40.000
they will take somewhere
between 300 and 600 milligrams

01:58:40.000 --> 01:58:41.690
that's more typical.

01:58:41.690 --> 01:58:43.670
Again, you have to check with your doctor,

01:58:43.670 --> 01:58:45.420
you have to decide if the safety margins

01:58:45.420 --> 01:58:47.120
are appropriate for you

01:58:47.120 --> 01:58:49.570
obviously you'll want to check that out,

01:58:49.570 --> 01:58:52.450
but alpha-GPC is effective in creating

01:58:52.450 --> 01:58:54.920
more focused by way of
this cholinergic system,

01:58:54.920 --> 01:58:56.790
It stimulates acetylcholine release

01:58:56.790 --> 01:58:58.940
from both of those locations,

01:58:58.940 --> 01:59:01.910
the PPN in the back of the
brain and nucleus basalis

01:59:01.910 --> 01:59:03.453
in the front of the brain.

01:59:04.300 --> 01:59:07.019
There are two other over
the counter compounds

01:59:07.019 --> 01:59:11.560
that are in active use out
there for treatment of ADHD

01:59:11.560 --> 01:59:15.541
and in use for simply
trying to improve focus

01:59:15.541 --> 01:59:17.660
and the first one is L-Tyrosine

01:59:17.660 --> 01:59:20.290
it's an amino acid that
acts as a precursor

01:59:20.290 --> 01:59:22.370
to the neuromodulator dopamine

01:59:22.370 --> 01:59:23.317
and now knowing everything you know about

01:59:23.317 --> 01:59:25.820
dopamine, attention and
the circuits involved,

01:59:25.820 --> 01:59:27.900
it should come as no surprise as to why

01:59:27.900 --> 01:59:31.310
people are exploring the use
of L-tyrosine for that purpose.

01:59:31.310 --> 01:59:34.373
L-tyrosine does lead to
increases in dopamine.

01:59:35.710 --> 01:59:40.060
They are fairly long lived
and L-tyrosine can improve

01:59:40.060 --> 01:59:42.870
one's ability to focus, however,

01:59:42.870 --> 01:59:46.110
the dosaging can be
very tricky to dial in.

01:59:46.110 --> 01:59:48.750
Sometimes it makes
people feel too euphoric

01:59:48.750 --> 01:59:51.510
or too jittery or too
alert that they are then

01:59:51.510 --> 01:59:52.957
unable to focus well.

01:59:52.957 --> 01:59:56.320
So the dosage ranges are huge,

01:59:56.320 --> 01:59:58.630
you see evidence for 100 milligrams

01:59:58.630 --> 02:00:00.900
all the way up to 1200 milligrams.

02:00:00.900 --> 02:00:01.733
It's something that really

02:00:01.733 --> 02:00:02.750
should be approached with caution,

02:00:02.750 --> 02:00:04.780
especially for people that have any kind

02:00:04.780 --> 02:00:07.560
of underlying psychiatric
or mood disorder,

02:00:07.560 --> 02:00:10.460
because dysregulation of
the dopamine system is

02:00:11.430 --> 02:00:15.420
central to many of the mood
disorders such as depression,

02:00:15.420 --> 02:00:19.080
but also especially
mania bipolar disorder,

02:00:19.080 --> 02:00:21.030
schizophrenia, things of that sort.

02:00:21.030 --> 02:00:22.680
So it's something that
really should be approached

02:00:22.680 --> 02:00:25.970
